SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.description:
The configuration to use for this command invocation. For more
information on how to use configurations, run:
`gcloud topic configurations`.  You can also use the [CLOUDSDK_ACTIVE_CONFIG_NAME] environment
variable to set the equivalent of this flag for a terminal
session.
SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.name: --configuration

SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.description: Specifies the amount of time until this image should become DELETED.
SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.name: --delete-in

SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.description: This flag is mutually exclusive with --delete-in.
SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.name: --delete-on

SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.description:
Flatten _name_[] output resource slices in _KEY_ into separate records
for each item in each slice. Multiple keys and slices may be specified.
This also flattens keys for *--format* and *--filter*. For example,
*--flatten=abc.def* flattens *abc.def[].ghi* references to
*abc.def.ghi*. A resource record containing *abc.def[]* with N elements
will expand to N records in the flattened output. This flag interacts
with other flags that are applied in this order: *--flatten*,
*--sort-by*, *--filter*, *--limit*.
SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.name: --flatten

SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.description:
Sets the format for printing command output resources. The default is a
command-specific human-friendly output format. The supported formats
are: `config`, `csv`, `default`, `diff`, `disable`, `flattened`, `get`, `json`, `list`, `multi`, `none`, `object`, `table`, `text`, `value`, `yaml`. For more details run $ gcloud topic formats.
SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.name: --format

SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.description: Log all HTTP server requests and responses to stderr. Overrides the default *core/log_http* property value for this command invocation.
SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.name: --log-http

SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.description: Log all HTTP server requests and responses to stderr.
SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.name: --no-log-http

SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.description: Print user intended output to the console.
SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.name: --no-user-output-enabled

SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.description: Specifies the amount of time until this image should become OBSOLETE.
SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.name: --obsolete-in

SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.description: This flag is mutually exclusive with --obsolete-in.
SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.name: --obsolete-on

SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.description:
Ordered Choices. _ORDERED_CHOICES_ must be one of:
+
*a-1g*::: first
*a-10g*::: second
*a-100g*::: third
+
SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.name: --ordered-choices

SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.description: Print user intended output to the console. Overrides the default *core/user_output_enabled* property value for this command invocation. Use *--no-user-output-enabled* to disable.
SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.name: --user-output-enabled

SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.description: Override the default verbosity for this command with any of the supported standard verbosity levels: `debug`, `info`, `warning`, `error`, and `none`. Overrides the default *core/verbosity* property value for this command invocation.
SERIALIZED_FLAG_LIST.name: --verbosity
